		<li class="" id="comment-45705">
		
		<h3 class="commenttitle"><a href='http://www.sugoodsweets.com/blog' rel='external nofollow' class='url'>Jessica "Su Good Sweets"</a> said,</h3>
			
		<p>Randa, you could probably use stevia or Splenda in the regular version, but significantly less, and it will alter the texture.  I don&#8217;t think it&#8217;d work in the caramel version though.  Coconut oil or cocoa butter probably won&#8217;t work, because they&#8217;re almost solid at room temp (and will make the choc hazelnut butter too stiff).  Also, I have a 7-cup Cuisinart food processor.  Have fun!</p>
		
		<p class="commentmeta">
		April 12, 2010 
		at <a href="#comment-45705">10:18 pm</a>
				</p>
		
